## Critical Application Rules

- `session_id` is composed as `{username}_{session_id_original}`, for example `toni.rc.neto@gmail.com_session-2`.
- Use `rfind("_session-")` or equivalent robust parsing. Do not use simple underscore splitting because usernames can contain underscores.
- Queries for `messages` and `conversations` must include both `session_id` and `username` whenever possible.
- Never return internal voice-service audio URLs directly to the browser. Use the gateway rewrite format `/api/voice/audio/{filename}`.
- Frontend `VITE_*` variables are build-time values and require rebuilds after changes.
- Prompts are initialized by the gateway startup flow. Prompt changes may need seed/update behavior, not only code changes.

## Medical And Mental Health Safety

When building the Medical AI Assistant direction:
- Focus on mental health support, psychoeducation, emotional reflection, self-awareness, care continuity, and preparation for professional help.
- Do not add behavior that diagnoses, prescribes, adjusts medication, or gives emergency medical instructions as if it were a clinician.
- Add escalation and crisis-support behavior for self-harm, suicide, abuse, psychosis, severe panic, and other high-risk signals.
- For physical medical symptoms, guide users to qualified care and emergency services when appropriate.
- Make uncertainty visible.
- Store safety metadata when adding safety classifiers, risk flags, or escalation flows.
- Prefer human review paths in admin tools for high-risk conversations.

## Agent And LLMOps Direction

Use the book in `docs/learning` as a conceptual guide for:
- Agent profiles/personas: mental health assistant, safety reviewer, session summarizer, clinician handoff writer.
- Actions/tools: chat, session context, emotion analysis, voice synthesis, retrieval, admin review.
- Memory/knowledge: session history, user profile, emotional timeline, approved mental-health educational material.
- Evaluation: prompt regression tests, safety test cases, grounding checks, response-quality rubrics.
- Planning/feedback: bounded workflows, clinician review, prompt improvement loops.

Avoid premature autonomy. In this app, autonomous behavior should be limited to bounded, reviewable tasks like summary generation, next-session suggestions, and evaluation workflows.

## English Learning Support

The user wants to learn English while building the project.
- Prefer clear English for technical docs, commit messages, and explanations.
- When useful, include short Portuguese clarification after English technical terms.
- Help build an engineering vocabulary around LLMOps, MLOps, agents, medical safety, and mental health support.
- Correct English gently when the user asks or when writing docs together.

## Publish Workflow

- When Codex completes code or documentation changes, commit the changes Codex made and push them to `origin/main`.
- Do not include unrelated user changes in commits.
- If the working tree contains unrelated modified or untracked files, leave them alone and only publish the files changed for the current task.
